    "client_msg_id": "01dc87b7-56b5-4f78-b6dc-b50cbf149a36",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Humane Tech Community:\n\n<https://community.humanetech.com>\n\nWhat I like about this is that it's mostly driven by stakeholders OTHER than programmers, who have recognize the need to improve the state of software / programming. That's invaluable perspective, since us tech guys are sometimes biased by our own needs vs how software can be changed to better serve humanity (business, users). I'm very hopeful that bringing more of \"us\" into their org may have great potential to bridge that gap and do the most good",
